name: Vintage Cameo Necklace, Almost Alice
description:
...one pill makes you small, one pill makes you tall...but I don't think the pill is anything at all...

Repurposed Vintage Ingredients: vintage glitter flocked cameo (that I took one glance & decided that 1. I had to have it & 2. she looks just like Alice in Wonderland (reinforcing the immediate reaction of "MINE"!).  1960's white floral  former clip on earring (back removed & sanded smooth) dangles from her. The necklace is made up of asymmetrical chains; one side is 1970's white teardrop links & gold chain, the other is heavy brass chain with 2 bezel set mid 1900's clip earrings. Pendant dangles 3"s & is 1.5"s at its widest. The necklace measures 16"s.

..."I can't explain myself, I'm afraid, Sir, because I'm not myself you see." Alice

Absolutely One of a Kind!!

name: Mother of Pearl Necklace, Full Moon
description:
...a full moon...no wonder everyone was acting all crazy today!

Repurposed Vintage Ingredients: one half of a swoon worthy antique brass & Mother of Pearl buckle gets a new life as a pendant. Vintage glass costume pearls were hand wired to create half the chain while two strands of vintage brass chain wrap around the other side of your neck. necklace is adjustable up to 18"s. For size reference the MOP piece (w/o the brass) is  1 3/4"s by 1 1/2"s.

"May you have warm words on a cold evening, a full moon on a dark night and a smooth road all the way to your door." Irish Blessing

Absolutely One of a Kind!!

name: Mercy Me No6
description:
...they always said she was such a saint...if only they knew the real truth...

Repurposed Vintage Ingredients: sterling silver Mary rosary charm holds up a  tassel of vintage & antique Italian religious charms: dainty sterling silver cross, a Catholic rosary cross, Ten Commandments charm "Thous Shall Not Take The Name of the Lord in Vain", silver Mary silhouette, & an ornate cross with saints  & dove in the middle.  Delicate silver chain completes the necklace.  Pendant dangles 5"s & the necklace measures a long 28"s & may be looped through itself to form a lariat style necklace (as shown in the first picture).

...mercy, mercy me, things aren't what they used to be! 

Absolutely One Of a Kind!!
